WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.680
Let's build a Python Web App together.

00:00:01.680 --> 00:00:05.000
With the holiday season coming up, there can be enough turmoil at the dinner table,

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:07.080
so let's avoid that during family movie night.

00:00:07.080 --> 00:00:09.940
Let's build a web app to help us fairly choose a family movie.

00:00:09.940 --> 00:00:13.200
This is a super simple application we can build using Shiny for Python.

00:00:13.200 --> 00:00:14.600
There are two key elements we need.

00:00:14.600 --> 00:00:17.379
First is the input so everyone can add their choice for the movie.

00:00:17.379 --> 00:00:20.040
And second is the random selector to choose the movie for the night.

00:00:20.040 --> 00:00:23.799
First, I'm adding the input for the movie submissions using a text element and button.

00:00:23.799 --> 00:00:27.180
The reactive event connected to this button will perform its function,

00:00:27.180 --> 00:00:28.840
thus adding the movie to the data table.

00:00:28.879 --> 00:00:32.279
Then we can add some logic for the randomized picker to help us select our movie.

00:00:32.279 --> 00:00:32.980
And there you have it!

00:00:32.980 --> 00:00:35.380
Stay tuned for part 2 where we can deploy this application.

00:00:35.380 --> 00:00:37.380
All along from our data science content, bye!

